A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending David Curtis Bridges, PhD, upon his induction into the
2 Georgia Agriculture Hall of Fame; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, David Curtis Bridges, PhD, has long been recognized by the citizens of this
4 state for the vital role that he has played in leadership and his deep personal commitment to
5 the welfare of the citizens of Georgia; and
6 WHEREAS, he has diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable hours of his time,
7 talents, and energy toward the betterment of his community and state as evidenced
8 dramatically by his legacy of agricultural education and rural advocacy; and
9 WHEREAS, from 2006 to 2022, David served as the 10th president of Abraham Baldwin
10 Agricultural College (ABAC), making him the longest serving college or university president
11 in Georgia; and
12 WHEREAS, he has worked tirelessly for many years on behalf of rural Georgia, and his
13 work with the Rural Caucus and the House Rural Development Council was instrumental in
14 creating the Center for Rural Prosperity and Innovation at ABAC; and
